I'm done saying I'm getting older. My new motto is "I'm becoming a CLASSIC"! Who's joining me? 🖤🤍✊🏽✨ #proud80sbaby #ageisastateofmind

Cheers to the last Friday of 2022! 💜🦷🪥✨

Fun fact: The official color for Dentistry is lilac, and it's also my favorite color. ☺️
Rest well... my sweet, sweet Mel! 💖#angelonearthnowinheaven #forevermysister

I know life comes at us HARD. Trust me, the last 2 weeks have been rough. But, you still have to be PRESENT and try to push through! 

One thing about me is that I genuinely LOVE to support others, and I get EXCITED seeing them shine ✨! That's why despite how much I grieve the loss of my dear sister Mel, I still showed up. And received an unexpected blessing! A musical bandaid. 

Don't forget to show up for others, put aside self, and be intentional in your POSITIVE support! You'd be surprised how much that person on the receiving end truly appreciates seeing you! ✊🏽✨

If you have an upcoming wedding or event, and need a singer. Check out @bobbi_storm her voice is amazing. A TRUE TALENT! 👌🏽✨
Fun, 70's style! ✨

Focus on the pursuit of ACTUALLY being happy. Not just looking like it!

Sending a huge hug to @tamika_thetherapist and @thestyleguru for curating and organizing this wonderful event.  Thank you for inviting me. We had a wonderful time having a much needed, GENUINE dialogue on REAL LIFE issues!! 

The goal is to be IT! Not, just look like IT. Whatever IT May be!

IG fam please keep pressing forward towards your "HAPPY"! Much love! 💚✨

#mayformentalhealth #greenformentalhealth #greenformentalhealthawareness💚 #mindbodystylelive
Can't believe I'm someone's momma! 2 at that! Grateful for the gift of motherhood, and that's a fact!!✨

Mother's Day weekend 2023. The best we could do lol! 🤷🏽‍♀️💙💖 #gowiththeflow #theyrejustchildren 

F.Y.I Millie took pics for dance earlier that day. Hence, the reason for the blue eyeshadow. You couldn't tell her nothing. Lol
Welp! I officially have a 3 year old daughter who picked out my entire outfit. 💖☺️✨

Just a gentle reminder to be intentional with spending time with your parents, loved ones and friends. 

Create positive memories. 

Live in the moment.  Be present. 

Ignore the negativity. 

Remain hopeful and optimistic. 

Dance. Even if you can't, or don't have rhythm. 

Sing. Even you can't hold a tune, or know the exact words. 

Laugh. With no reservations. 

Cry, if necessary. 
 
Let your Guard down. Don't be so hard on yourself, or others. 

Count your blessings. 

Learn from the past, but don't live there! 

Love all of you. The good, the bad, the imperfections. 

Lean, Trust and Rely on God! 🙏🏽🙌🏽
Swipe to the 3rd slide to see my greatest accomplishments!! 😊❤️💙💛💚✨

Just me on a beautiful Sunny day
Reminiscing 
Reliving 
The days when I said I wanted to be dentist 
People laughed, people doubted 
But, in the midst I SPROUTED! 
To my ppl with wishes
To my ppl with visions 
Keep pushing forward, and don't listen 
To the naysayers 
Or the Bone carriers
Realize your potential 
Keep moving forward 
With or without rewards.
Do you, that's the best you'll ever do!

F.y.i I just wrote this off the top of my head. Those close to me know that I used to keep a journal of poems and rhymes. 

I only want to see everyone succeed! ❤️💪🏽✨ #purposefulimperfections

My favorite takeaway from the Barbie movie 

"It is literally impossible to be a woman. You are so beautiful, and so smart, and it kills me that you don’t think you’re good enough. Like, we have to always be extraordinary, but somehow we’re always doing it wrong.
You have to be thin, but not too thin. And you can never say you want to be thin. You have to say you want to be healthy, but also you have to be thin. You have to have money, but you can’t ask for money because that’s crass. You have to be a boss, but you can’t be mean. You have to lead, but you can’t squash other people’s ideas. You’re supposed to love being a mother, but don’t talk about your kids all the damn time. You have to be a career woman, but also always be looking out for other people. You have to answer for men’s bad behavior, which is insane, but if you point that out, you’re accused of complaining. You’re supposed to stay pretty for men, but not so pretty that you tempt them too much or that you threaten other women because you’re supposed to be a part of the sisterhood. But always stand out and always be grateful. But never forget that the system is rigged. So find a way to acknowledge that but also always be grateful. You have to never get old, never be rude, never show off, never be selfish, never fall down, never fail, never show fear, never get out of line. It’s too hard! It’s too contradictory and nobody gives you a medal or says thank you! And it turns out in fact that not only are you doing everything wrong, but also everything is your fault.
I’m just so tired of watching myself and every single other woman tie herself into knots so that people will like us. And if all of that is also true for a doll just representing women, then I don’t even know." -America Ferrera 

@beautybandit_ashley Thanks so much to you and your tribe for executing the amazing Barbie Experience yesterday we had a ball! 💖✨
And so begins Chapter 39 ✨ #aug2

Throughout my 11 year professional career span I have dedicated my time, energy and focus towards mentorship, community service, servicing the underserved and being a representation for people of color. 

I NEVER want my presence in this world to be in vain. That's why I always put the work in. Whether it's showcased or not. Everything comes FULL CIRCLE. 

Receiving any accolades was never on my radar. I give back from the heart. That's why I am truly humbled, yet delighted to be recognized as one of the Michigan Chronicle 40under40 2023 Honorees. 

Congratulations to all the other honorees, and a heartfelt thank you to the @michiganchronicle for this distinguished honor.

Last night I was emotional, yet quiet. Soaking in all the amazing stories that OUR people have woven into FRUITION. Stories of people being BOLD, UNAPOLOGETIC and FEARLESS. 💪🏽✨

I am honored, proud,  and humbled to be amongst these trailblazers. Most of all... I'm INSPIRED! This isn't the end! Congratulations to all the other Michigan Chronicle 40under40 recipients. It's well deserved! 🖤💪🏽✨

I was excited for my babies to witness all that BLACK excellence in one room. You may think "Nah, they're too young they won't remember that night". But, I say that's not true❗️ My babies are STILL singing "Happy Graduation 🎵 "! I thought that was the cutest thing.  Because they felt the energy, they felt inspiration, they felt the vibes. 

My babies have given me a RESURGENCE. Before them everything I did was for myself. NOW, everything I do is for them. Because of them, I won't ever stop!! It's only the beginning! 🖤💪🏽✨ 

Major shoutout to my family and friends for ALWAYS supporting me. I love you with ALL my ❤️. A HUGE thank you to the @michiganchronicle for charging that battery in my back!! Most of all I give God ALL the GLORY! 🙌🏽✊🏽🖤✨ #michiganchronicle mchonors2023 #michiganchronicle2023

This post is dedicated to my mom @runbully_t . IG fam If you've read my book 'Purposeful Imperfections' you're aware of her testimony. If you haven't, I've provided  a little bit of her story in this video. She is my SHERO, and quite the OVERCOMER. So to witness her check each goal off the running checklist is a blessing for me. To go from being told that she would NEVER be able to walk again, and now to QUALIFYING & RUNNING in MAJOR ones ... Chicago and Berlin Marathons to be exact is a true testament of Gods healing, grace, mercy and favor! I'm in COMPLETE AWE! ❤️🥰

Thank you to all of her running buddies @distracteddetroitrunner (and more) for supporting her, and to my Soror @my_sisters_keypers for capturing her cross the finish line. This is huge. Wish I could've been there! 

IG fam I'll leave you with my moms favorite Bible scripture.  1 Corinthians 9:26 "So I run with purpose in every step. I am not just shadowboxing." NLT #purposefulimperfections  #herwinsaremywins #weareovercomers #fleetambassador
